  }
  ...
}
```
If you call `getScore` for a hole which you haven&#39;t set a score for yet, it will throw a `NullPointerException`, because the value in the `Map` for that hole will be `null`. That will tell you that you have a logic bug in your program, and you are trying to use a value before you&#39;ve set it. Finding that out is usually a good thing.

